  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>A lot of sites nowadays use a service called Gravatar: <a href="http://en.gravatar.com/">http://en.gravatar.com/</a>
I don't know the technical details, but I guess Gravatar keeps a map from email
addresses to images (profile pictures). Then if you sign up for a site that uses
Gravatar, by putting in your email address you automatically have a profile
picture on that site.

If OpenHatch used Gravatar then I think a lot more people would have profile
pictures instead of that little default bird image (cute though it may be, I admit).

I've never used Gravatar, but I imagine it's fairly easy to set up.
<a href="http://en.gravatar.com/site/implement/">http://en.gravatar.com/site/implement/</a> would be the place to start, it seems.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
